Package com.atakmap.spatial

Class CoverageAccumulator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.atakmap.spatial.CoverageAccumulator
  • public class CoverageAccumulator
extends java.lang.Object
    Helper class used to accumulate and union boundries into a single polygonal bounding box. This class uses a SpatialCalculator behind the scenes to do it's calculations.

    • Constructor Detail

      • CoverageAccumulator

        public CoverageAccumulator​(SpatialCalculator calculator)
        Creates a CoverageAccumulator instance backed by a provided SpatialCalculator. This allows the creation of a CoverageAccumulator that does not use a static instance of SpatialCalculator to back it. When using this constructor, the user is responsible for cleanup/disposal of the provided SpatialCalculator.
        Parameters:
        calculator - SpatialCalculator to back this CoverageAccumulator with. If this value is null, a static instance of SpatialCalculator will be used. Calling this method with null is functionally equivalent to calling #CoverageAccumulator().

      • addBounds

        public void addBounds​(byte[] geometryBlob)
        Adds a geometric bounding box to the overall bounding polygon currently being accumulated.
        Parameters:
        geometryBlob - Blob of geometric data stored in the spatialite blob format. This method is suitable for use with data directly returned by the SpatialCalculator.getGeometryAsBlob(long) method.

      • addBounds

        public void addBounds​(Geometry geometry)
        Adds a geometric bounding box to the overall bounding polygon currently being accumulated.
        Parameters:
        geometry - Geometry object that will be converted to wkb format before being added to the accumulated area.

      • addWkbBounds

        public void addWkbBounds​(byte[] wkbGeometry)
        Adds a geometric bounding box to the overall bounding polygon currently being accumulated.
        Parameters:
        wkbGeometry - Blob of geometric data stored in the WKB (Well Known Blob) format. Suitable for use with data returned by the Geometry.toWkb(java.nio.ByteBuffer) method of a class extending the Geometry abstract class.

      • clear

        public void clear()
        Clears the geometry/bounding boxes for this CoverageAccumulator. If this CoverageAccumulator is backed by a static SpatialCalculator instance, this method will not effect the bounding boxes of other instances of CoverageAccumulator also backed by that same static instance.

      • getCoverageGeometryBlob

        public byte[] getCoverageGeometryBlob()
        Gets the current combined coverage of all bounding boxes that have been added to this instance.
        Returns:
        Geometry data stored in the spatialite blob format. This data can be transformed into Geometry instances using the GeometryFactory.parseSpatiaLiteBlob(byte[]) method.

      • addGSD

        public void addGSD​(double gsd)
        Adds a GSD to be tracked by this CoverageAccumulator. This GSD will automatically be classified as either a max or min GSD, if appropriate.
        Parameters:
        gsd - Ground Sample Distance in Meters per Pixel.

      • getMinGSD

        public double getMinGSD()
        Get the minimum ground sample distance for this area of coverage. This value is not calculated from data added by the addBounds(byte[]) or methods, but is instead based on data added through the {@link #addGSD(double)} method.
        Returns:
        Minimum Ground Sample Distance for this area of coverage in Meters per Pixel.

      • getMaxGSD

        public double getMaxGSD()
        Get the maximum ground sample distance for this area of coverage. This value is not calculated from data added by the addBounds(byte[]) or methods, but is instead based on data added through the {@link #addGSD(double)} method.
        Returns:
        Maximum Ground Sample Distance for this area of coverage in Meters per Pixel.
